On August 21, 2019, the President signed into law several bills designating various United States Postal Service facilities with new names. The facilities include the Louise and Bob Slaughter Post Office in Fairport, New York; the Congressman Bill Carney Post Office in Smithtown, New York; the Army Specialist Thomas J. Wilwerth Post Office Building in Mastic, New York; the Henderson Veterans Memorial Post Office Building in Henderson, Nevada; the Captain Robert L. Martin Post Office in Olympia Fields, Illinois; and the Ryan Keith Cox Post Office Building in Virginia Beach, Virginia.